						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in front of the Vīrabhadrasvāmi temple situated to the west of the village.</p>						

						<p>1850 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in Śaka 1772, Saumya, Āshāḍha, ba. 10, corresponding to 1849 A.D., June 30, Saturday.</p>						

						<p>States that Pullabattuḍu son of Charlabaḍla Vīranna and his wife Pullamma constructed the sanctuṁ sanctorun <hi rend="italic">(garbhagaḍi)</hi> and Vitappa son of Chinvīranna engraved the inscription.</p>						

						</summary>
